snippet.textDisplay:
*The only reason why it's an "anomaly in Apple's Business model" is because any software they produce is intended to fit and work within the Apple ecosystem.*

Theoretically, Apple, if they wanted to restrict its use, could have its search engine detect what browser, OS and/or device is being used, and if it's Safari, OSX / iOS and/or an iPhone / iPad / MacBook / iMac device, they're allowed access. Another solution would be to sign into your Apple account to use the search engine. Although, the added level of complexity from the second option may frustrate and deter Apple users.
